  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research settings to predict hemolysis indices for centrifugal blood pumps operating under ventricular assist device conditions. The CFD hemolysis model targets the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry and was exercised across a range of operating points representative of VAD therapy. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all 13 credibility factors defined in ASME V&V 40-2018. Seven factors were formally assessed; six remain flagged as epistemic gaps at Model Risk Level 5. Despite these gaps, the aggregate credibility evidence was judged sufficient for the intended engineering decision at the Low assurance level under the Minimal profile. No structured Context of Use object is attached to this unit of assurance; intended-use scope is conveyed only through the narrative above.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-low-assurance",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-vad-cou2",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-hemolysis",
